{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-chapter-level-2-chapter-level-2-tsx","path":"/topics/bunions/diagnosis/diagnosis/","result":{"pageContext":{"chapter":{"id":"e4655e40-6e10-5221-9d9e-90c2c9e717df","slug":"diagnosis","fullItemName":"Diagnosis","depth":2,"htmlHeader":"<!-- begin field 87f08932-bca5-4f9b-a151-dc85a685ff3e --><h2>How should I diagnose bunions?</h2><!-- end field 87f08932-bca5-4f9b-a151-dc85a685ff3e -->","summary":"","htmlStringContent":"<!-- begin item 2e592c94-cb8d-4694-8945-884e9c99f8b7 --><!-- begin field 59ef54a3-37d4-473f-a65e-a3fffbfd1f78 --><ul><li>The diagnosis of a bunion is usually based on clinical findings. Note that not all people with bunions have symptoms.</li><li>Examine the person both sitting down and standing (standing up may exaggerate the deformity). Look for:<br></li><ul><li>Lateral deviation of the first toe at the metatarsophalangeal (MTP) joint. </li><li>Movement of the first toe towards the second toe.</li><li>Prominence of the first metatarsal head.</li><li>Medial bursitis over the first MTP joint (as a result of irritation from shoes).</li></ul></ul><!-- end field 59ef54a3-37d4-473f-a65e-a3fffbfd1f78 --><!-- end item 2e592c94-cb8d-4694-8945-884e9c99f8b7 -->","topic":{"id":"76b2380a-acc4-5a53-abbc-54dc4e820023","topicId":"d5d4a5aa-b173-494b-a00c-c612bd839f16","topicName":"Bunions","slug":"bunions","lastRevised":"Last revised in August 2016","chapters":[{"id":"e5f36e2f-a744-5067-89db-65287a937581","fullItemName":"Summary","slug":"summary","subChapters":[]},{"id":"5ad8f8cb-83d8-579e-a1f2-d562fecf8456","fullItemName":"Have I got the right topic?","slug":"have-i-got-the-right-topic","subChapters":[]},{"id":"37478665-f397-50a1-9d8e-35634971bda3","fullItemName":"How up-to-date is this topic?","slug":"how-up-to-date-is-this-topic","subChapters":[{"id":"e05ade73-827d-58c1-a280-051cbb74e03b","slug":"changes","fullItemName":"Changes"},{"id":"12f02182-caa3-5914-b285-53d34d2940d0","slug":"update","fullItemName":"Update"}]},